2ª via de Boletos






Healthy Products 
We invest in research and in innovation to create healthier products for everyone.















Healthy Products 
We invest in research and in innovation to create healthier products for everyone, without the consumers leave eating foods which they like.



Share


















Font size

Decrease font size
Increase font size



We work continuously to improve the flavor and the nutritional content of the foods we produce and which reach more than 110 countries. In Brazil, we are aligned with the ABIA (Brazilian Association of Food Industries) standards and Ministry of Health standards.
BRF's goal is to develop healthier products, combat the main nutritional villains and tie its product launches to strict quality and food security criteria.
Since 2008, we have worked at eliminating the use of trans fat in our formulations. This action demanded intense research and sensory, performance, and food security tests in all categories of BRF's product portfolio.
We are reducing the percentages of sodium in products with investments in new technologies for developing ingredients and that contribute to food preservation. We have already reduced the amount of salt in hamburgers, nuggets, mortadela, margarine, sausages and frankfurters, lasagnas and other hot dishes.
We have also reduced the sugar content in dairy products, using substitute ingredients to obtain that sweet flavor - fructose or artificial sweeteners - with fewer calories. Furthermore, fructose does not need the insulin hormone to be absorbed, differing from glucose, which is formed during metabolism of sucrose.
With these measures in the food production phase, we want to offer consumers healthier products that can be consumed at any time of the day.


